cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a novel deep network architecture for volumetric brain segmentation, which is a task related to computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The proposed network architecture is based on densely convolutional networks, which is a popular technique in deep learning (DL) and machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of multi-scale contextual information, which is a common technique in neural networks for natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision. Therefore, cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper focuses on brain MRI segmentation, which is a medical imaging application. Therefore, cs.MM (medical imaging) is another possible sub-category.
